# Second brain — Garrett's private operational layer (tracked separately via 'brain' remote)
# Root CLAUDE.md is now committed (project-wide conventions for all contributors + Claude Code).
# Team-shared institutional context lives in TEAM.md; team conventions in CONTRIBUTING.md.
# Specific .brain/ files (TASKS.md, memory/handoff/*) are force-tracked via `git add -f`
# as collision-surface infrastructure — see .brain/memory/handoff/README.md.
# CLAUDE.md is personal/per-developer by default — keep machine-specific Claude
# instructions out of commits so they don't leak across the team or get swept up
# by `git add -A` (e.g. wv-handoff). Shared CLAUDE.md files are force-tracked
# (`git add -f`); the ones already committed are re-included here so they stay tracked.
CLAUDE.md
!/CLAUDE.md
!apps/nordic-sqr-rct/CLAUDE.md
!docs/cmo/CLAUDE.md
.brain/

# Nested git repos — Phase A.2 dissolved port/ nested-clone 2026-05-01
# port/ is now tracked as ordinary monorepo content

# Wrangler local state
.wrangler/

# Supabase CLI link-state cache (generated by `supabase link` — never commit)
**/supabase/.temp/

# Sensitive env files (created by Vercel CLI or manual — never commit)
.env.port-check
*.env.production
*.env.vercel

# locally-generated booking secrets — never commit
.secrets-do-not-commit/
*/.secrets-do-not-commit/
.vercel
